%20and%20Gay's%20plagiarism%20have%20more%20similarities%20than%20differences%2C%20according%20to%20experts%20and%20an%20internal%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGay%20was%20accused%2C%20accurately%20in%20at%20least%20some%20of%20the%20cases%2C%20of%20using%20verbatim%20text%20from%20outside%20sources%20and%2C%20though%20in%20most%20cases%20the%20source%20was%20cited%2C%20it%20was%20not%20marked%20as%20quoted%20text%2C%26quot%3B%20Jonathan%20Bailey%2C%20a%20plagiarism%20expert%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThat%20seems%20to%20be%20pretty%20much%20what%20happened%20here%20with%20Oxman.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20authors%20made%20mistakes%20in%20their%20papers%2C%20Bailey%20said%2C%20but%20a%20handful%20of%20improper%20citations%20found%20in%20a%20research%20paper%20or%20dissertation%20spanning%20a%20couple%20hundred%20pages%20would%20not%20typically%20rise%20to%20the%20level%20of%20termination%20in%20academia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20kind%20of%20plagiarism%20%26quot%3Busually%20comes%20not%20so%20much%20from%20a%20malicious%20intent%20to%20steal%2C%20but%20from%20a%20very%2C%20very%20soppy%20writing%20style%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20the%20two%20stack%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENeither%20Oxman%20nor%20Gay%20are%20accused%20of%20stealing%20big%20ideas%20%E2%80%94%20but%20their%20works%20do%20contain%20citation%20inadequacies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20issue%20for%20both%20Gay%20and%20Oxman%20has%20to%20do%20with%20quotation%20marks%3A%20The%20two%20included%20direct%20passages%20cribbed%20from%20other%20academics%2C%20and%20while%20they%20cited%20their%20sources%20in%20line%20and%20included%20the%20sources%20in%20their%20bibliographies%2C%20the%20passages%20were%20not%20put%20in%20quotes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBelow%20is%20a%20passage%20from%20a%20paper%20by%20Israeli%20scholars%20Steve%20Weiner%20and%20H.%20Daniel%20Wagner%20alongside%20a%20passage%20from%20Oxman's%20dissertation%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22comp%20wiener%20and%20wanger%20and%20oxman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659722991c5c7b8c9a0e1e12%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222072%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20comparison%2C%20first%20identified%20by%20Christopher%20Rufo%2C%20a%20conservative%20activist%2C%20and%20Christopher%20Brunet%2C%20a%20contributing%20editor%20at%20The%20American%20Conservative%2C%20shows%20Gay%20failing%20to%20put%20quotation%20marks%20around%20a%20passage%20from%20Lawrence%20Bobo%20and%20Franklin%20D.%20Gilliam's%20%26quot%3BRace%2C%20Sociopolitical%20Participation%2C%20and%20Black%20Empowerment%26quot%3B%20in%20her%201997%20Harvard%20dissertation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BThe%20results%20show%20that%20blacks%20in%20high-black-empowerment%20areas-as%20indicated%20by%20control%20of%20the%20mayor's%20office-are%20more%20active%20than%20either%20blacks%20living%20in%20low-empowerment%20areas%20or%20their%20white%20counterparts%20of%20comparable%20socioeconomic%20status.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20results%20show%20that%20empowerment%20influences%20black%20participation%20by%20contributing%20to%20a%20more%20trusting%20and%20efficacious%20orientation%20to%20politics%20and%20by%20greatly%20increasing%20black%20attentiveness%20to%20political%20affairs.%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3ELawrence%20Bobo%20and%20Franklin%20D.%20Gilliam%2C%20Jr.%20in%20%26quot%3BRace%2C%20Sociopolitical%20Participation%2C%20and%20Black%20Empowerment%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BUsing%201987%20survey%20data%2C%20Bobo%20and%20Gilliam%20found%20that%20African-Americans%20in%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20black-empowerment%26quot%3B%20areas%E2%80%94as%20indicated%20by%20control%20of%20the%20mayor's%20office%E2%80%94are%20more%20active%20than%20either%20African-Americans%20in%20low%20empowerment%20areas%20or%20their%20white%20counterparts%20of%20comparable%20socioeconomic%20status.%20Empowerment%2C%20they%20conclude%2C%20influences%20black%20participation%20by%20contributing%20to%20a%20more%20trusting%20and%20efficacious%20orientation%20towards%20politics%20and%20by%20greatly%20increasing%20black%20attentiveness%20to%20political%20affairs.%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3EClaudine%20Gay%20in%20%26quot%3BTaking%20Charge%3A%20Black%20Electoral%20Success%20and%20the%20Redefinition%20of%20American%20Policies%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20omitting%20quotation%20marks%20violated%20MIT's%20academic%20integrity%20code%20at%20the%20time%20of%20Oxman's%20dissertation%20and%20is%20against%20Harvard's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fusingsources.fas.harvard.edu%2Fharvard-plagiarism-policy%23%3A~%3Atext%3DStudents%2520who%252C%2520for%2520whatever%2520reason%2Cto%2520withdraw%2520from%2520the%2520College.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecurrent%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20experts%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0including%20scholars%20whose%20work%20Gay%20and%20Oxman%20copied%20%E2%80%94%20have%20largely%20agreed%20the%20offense%20is%20inconsequential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20researchers%20make%20this%20type%20of%20mistake%2C%20a%20typical%20course%20of%20action%20might%20be%20to%20issue%20a%20correction%20and%20perhaps%20take%20a%20remedial%20course%20on%20research%20writing%2C%20Bailey%2C%20the%20plagiarism%20expert%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20Gay%20and%20for%20Oxman%2C%20there's%20no%20real%20pattern%20to%20what%20sentence%20is%20used%2C%26quot%3B%20Bailey%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20both%20of%20these%20cases%20could%20be%20a%20case%20where%20the%20author%20pulled%20text%20and%20forgot%20to%20put%20it%20in%20quotes%20or%20intended%20to%20paraphrase%20but%20forgot%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGay%20requested%20several%20corrections%20to%20her%20papers%20after%20the%20citation%20erro