20publicly%20apologized%20for%20that%20on%20X%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BRest%20assured%20that%20her%20apology%20is%20accepted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarol%20Swain%2C%20a%20former%20Vanderbilt%20University%20professor%2C%20did%2C%20however%2C%20express%20dismay%20at%20Gay's%20mistakes%20and%20admonished%20her%20and%20Harvard%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fclaudine-gay-and-my-scholarship-plagiarism-elite-system-unearned-position-24e4a1b1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20op-ed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMs.%20Gay's%20damage%20to%20me%20is%20aggravated%20because%20her%20early%20work%20was%20in%20the%20area%20where%20my%20research%20is%20considered%20seminal.%20Her%20scholarship%20on%20black%20congressional%20representation%2C%20electoral%20districting%20and%20descriptive%20representation%20builds%20on%20terrain%20where%20I%20plowed%20the%20ground%2C%26quot%3B%20Swain%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBoth%20Oxman%20and%20Gay%20copied%20language%20almost%20word-for-word%2C%20without%20any%20citation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20330-page%20dissertation%2C%20Oxman%20pulled%20a%20paragraph%2C%20almost%20word-for-word%2C%20from%20a%20book%20published%20in%201998%20by%20German%20physicist%20Claus%20Mattheck%20without%20quotation%20or%20attribution.%20In%20the%20post%20on%20X%2C%20Oxman%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20deeply%20apologize%20to%20Mattheck%20for%20inadvertently%20not%20citing%20him%20when%20I%20paraphrased.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22comp%20Matthech%20and%20Oxman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659722c76979d737182091a6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222295%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGay%20faces%20some%20of%20the%20same%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20complaint%20sent%20to%20Havard%20claimed%20that%20her%201993%20article%20%26quot%3BBetween%20Black%20and%20White%3A%20The%20Complexity%20of%20Brazilian%20Race%20Relations%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20journal%20Origins%20contained%20numerous%20passages%20of%20text%20that%20closely%20mirrored%20writing%20by%20scholar%20David%20Covin%20without%20any%20mention%20of%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Gay%20wrote%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fundamental%20organizational%20unit%2C%20as%20approved%20by%20the%20founding%20National%20Assembly%20in%201978%2C%20was%20to%20be%20the%20Center%20of%20Struggle%20(Centro%20de%20Luta).%20Centers%20were%20to%20be%20formed%20in%20work%20areas%2C%20villages%2C%20prisons%2C%20candomble%20and%20umbanda%20temples%2C%20samba%20schools%2C%20churches%2C%20and%20favelas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%201990%20article%20titled%20%26quot%3BAfrocentricity%20in%20O%20Movimento%20Negro%20Unificado%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20Journal%20of%20Black%2C%20Covin%2C%20by%20comparison%2C%20wrote%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20basic%20organizational%20structure%20which%20they%20approved%2C%20the%20Centers%20of%20Struggle%20were%20the%20fundamental%20organizational%20units.%20These%20were%20to%20be%20formed%20in%20work%20areas%2C%20villages%2C%20prisons%2C%20candombl%C3%A9%20and%20umbanda%20temples%2C%20samba%20schools%2C%20afox%C3%A9s%2C%20churches%2C%20and%20favelas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGay's%20plagiarism%20problems%20go%20beyond%20her%20dissertation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGay's%20citation%20issues%20extend%20beyond%20her%20dissertation%20and%20to%20her%20academic%20writing.%20Eight%20of%20her%20published%20works%20have%20been%20flagged%20to%20Harvard%20for%20containing%20instances%20of%20plagiarism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20has%20analyzed%20Oxman's%20dissertation%20for%20plagiarism%2C%20not%20her%20entire%20body%20of%20academic%20writings%2C%20and%20there%20has%20been%20much%20greater%20scrutiny%20of%20Gay's%20writing%20than%20Oxman's.%20So%20far%2C%20instances%20of%20plagiarism%20have%20only%20been%20reported%20as%20an%20issue%20in%20Oxman's%20dissertation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBailey%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Oxman%20and%20Gay%20exemplified%20%26quot%3Bpoor%20writing%20habits%26quot%3B%20that%20he%20often%20sees%20in%20students%20who%20make%20citation%20a%20part%20of%20the%20editing%20process%20rather%20than%20the%20writing%20task.%20Cite%20as%20you%20write%20to%20avoid%20making%20these%20types%20of%20mistakes%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20indicates%20a%20bad%20process%20to%20drafting%20this%20stuff%2C%20and%20I%20would%20say%20that's%20true%20for%20both%20Gay%20and%20Oxman%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it%20doesn't%20necessarily%2C%20in%20either%20case%2C%20represent%20a%20malicious%20desire%20to%20take%20the%20work%20of%20others%20and%20not%20give%20them%20credit%20for%20it.%20It's%20just%20poor%20writing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaudine-gay-neri-oxman-ackman-wife-plagiarism-dissertation-harvard-mit-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704432411000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65976dec1c5c7b8c9a0e318a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaudine-gay-neri-oxman-ackman-wife-plagiarism-dissertation-harvard-mit-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20works%20of%20former%20Harvard%20president%20Claudine%20Gay%20and%20Neri%20Oxman%2C%20an%20academic%20and%20Bill%20Ackman's%20wife%2C%20include%20very%20similar%20citation%20errors.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lloydlee%40insider.com%20(Lloyd%20Lee%2CMadeline%20Berg)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaudine-gay-neri-oxman-ackman-wife-plagiarism-dissert