-parent-signs-psychologist-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eemotionally%20immature%20parents%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20reactive%20parents%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsigns-symptoms-you-are-struggling-with-emotional-dysregulation-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edifficulty%20regulating%20their%20emotions%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20whether%20they%20feel%20anger%2C%20frustration%2C%20or%20sadness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20become%20the%20person%20in%20the%20family%20that%20everyone%20else%20tiptoes%20around%20because%20nobody%20wants%20to%20set%20them%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20Gibson%20said.%20%26quot%3BVery%20emotional%20parents%2C%20psychologically%20speaking%2C%20are%20using%20other%20people%20as%20containers%20for%20their%20emotional%20upset.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%20in%20this%20kind%20of%20environment%20can%20have%20vast%20emotional%20consequences%2C%20shaping%20how%20you%20deal%20with%20conflict%20and%20how%20you%20experience%20your%20own%20emotions.%20Gibson%20shared%20some%20of%20the%20signs%20you%20grew%20up%20with%20a%20reactive%20parent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20You%20hold%20in%20your%20emotions%20without%20even%20realizing%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20parent%20having%20free%20rein%20on%20how%20they%20express%20their%20anger%20or%20anxiety%20comes%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20their%20child%2C%20Gibson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20children%20feel%20like%20they%20have%20to%20take%20in%20and%20contain%20the%20parent's%20distress%20or%20the%20parent's%20rage%2C%26quot%3B%20Gibson%20said.%20Even%20if%20the%20child%20feels%20scared%2C%20annoyed%2C%20or%20stressed%2C%20they%20learn%20from%20an%20early%20age%20that%20it's%20more%20important%20to%20keep%20it%20together%20on%20the%20outside%20and%20tend%20to%20their%20parent%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20this%20dynamic%2C%20%26quot%3Bemotional%20parents%20often%20create%20very%20self-sacrificing%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20Gibson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20You're%20always%20on%20the%20lookout%20for%20any%20hint%20of%20conflict%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20side%20effects%20of%20having%20a%20volatile%20parent%20is%20becoming%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhow-to-stop-being-a-people-pleaser-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epeople-pleaser%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Gibson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKids%20in%20these%20environments%20learn%20that%20%26quot%3Bif%20they%20can%20calm%20that%20parent%20down%20or%20put%20that%20parent%20first%2C%20they%20stand%20a%20much%20higher%20likelihood%20of%20having%20a%20more%20peaceful%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20they%20have%20to%20constantly%20have%20one%20eye%20out%20for%20that%20parent's%20emotional%20status%20so%20that%20it%20doesn't%20escalate%20into%20some%20kind%20of%20outburst.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20they%20grow%20up%2C%20children%20of%20reactive%20parents%20become%20hypervigilant%20by%20default%2C%20even%20when%20they're%20not%20with%20their%20parents%2C%20and%20are%20excellent%20at%20reading%20people%20and%20situations.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20a%20person%20is%20about%20to%20get%20upset%2C%20they%20know%20how%20to%20come%20in%20and%20soothe%20things%20or%20make%20sure%20they%20don't%20say%20the%20wrong%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20Gibson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOften%2C%20these%20children%20don't%20even%20notice%20how%20often%20they%20scan%20their%20surroundings%2C%20she%20said.%20They%20become%20naturals%20at%20tuning%20into%20everyone%20else's%20emotions%20but%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20You%20can%20be%20drawn%20to%20%26quot%3Bloose%20cannon%26quot%3B%20friends%20and%20partners%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20relationships%20with%20our%20parents%20can%20heavily%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fparents-affect-romantic-relationships-choose-partner-similar-traits-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20influence%20our%20other%20relationships%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20from%20romantic%20to%20platonic.%20Because%20these%20children%20are%20used%20to%20doing%20the%20emotional%20work%20for%20their%20parents%2C%20Gibson%20said%20they%20can%20end%20up%20choosing%20friends%20and%20romantic%20partners%20who%20make%20them%20feel%20the%20same%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20may%20pick%20a%20best%20friend%20who%20is%20kind%20of%20a%20loose%20cannon%2C%20or%20they%20might%20be%20attracted%20to%20a%20very%20passionate-seeming%20partner%20because%20that's%20attractive%20to%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Gibson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20it%20has%20to%20do%20with%20how%20kids%20of%20reactive%20parents%20define%20their%20own%20sense%20of%20self-worth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGibson%20said%20that%20everyone%20wants%20to%20feel%20useful%20in%20relationships%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bif%20your%20effectiveness%20is%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20helping%20other%20people%20to%20stay%20stable%20and%20to%20not%20get%20overly%20upset%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20be%20drawn%20into%20relationships%20where%20that's%20needed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Your%20parent%20still%20tries%20to%20control%20your%20adult%20life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20reactive%20parent%20is%20still%20alive%2C%20their%20explosive%20personality%20might%20still%20take%20hold%20of%20your%20life%2C%20even%20if%20you're%20an%20adult%20and%20live%20far%20away%2C%20Gibson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20you%20find%20a%20partner%2C%20there%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Btremendous%20conflict%26quot%3B%20because%20your%20parent%20can%20berate%20and%20try%20to%20guilt-trip%20you%20into%20choosing%20between%20them%20or%20your%20new%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGibson%20said%20she's%20had%20several%20clients%20who%20still%20feel%20controlled%20by%20parents%20who%20are%20%26quot%3Bstill%20calling%20the%20shots%