ill%20Pannun%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20an%20Indian%20intelligence%20official.%20He%20was%20arrested%20in%20June%20last%20year%20and%20Czech%20courts%20are%20considering%20his%20extradition%2C%20as%20requested%20by%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Dipankar%20Datta%20also%20concurred%20with%20the%20view%20of%20his%20fellow%20judge.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20examined%20the%20prayers%20made%20in%20the%20present%20writ%20petition.%20Keeping%20in%20view%20the%20principles%20of%20public%20international%20law%20and%20sovereignty%20and%20comity%20of%20courts%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20any%20of%20the%20prayers%20can%20be%20granted.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20Gupta%E2%80%99s%20kin%20told%20the%20court%20the%20events%20leading%20up%20to%20his%20arrest%20had%20been%20marked%20by%20%E2%80%9Cirregularities%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CFrom%20the%20outset%2C%20the%20petitioner%20contends%20that%20the%20circumstances%20surrounding%20his%20arrest%20were%20marked%20by%20irregularities%2C%20with%20no%20formal%20arrest%20warrant%20presented%2C%20and%20the%20apprehension%20executed%20by%20self-claimed%20US%20agents%20rather%20than%20local%20Czech%20authorities%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20petition%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-rejects-petition-by-family-members-of-nikhil-gupta-indicted-by-us-in-pannun-murder-plot-101704346298067.html%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20petitioner%20was%20not%20shown%20any%20arrest%20warrant%20during%20the%20initial%20detention.%20Instead%2C%20he%20found%20himself%20in%20the%20custody%20of%20individuals%20purporting%20to%20represent%20US%20interests%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20petition%20further%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20a%20submission%20by%20Gupta%E2%80%99s%20counsel%2C%20C.%20Aryama%20Sundaram%2C%20Justice%20Khanna%20stated%20that%20all%20aspects%20of%20the%20matter%20in%20question%