e%20Divine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20modern%20constitutions%20are%20based%20on%20the%20theory%20that%20sovereignty%20resides%20with%20the%20people%20to%20be%20exercised%20in%20our%20interest%20by%20our%20elected%20representatives.%20They%20bear%20distinctive%20features%20that%20encode%20liberal%20norms%20and%20most%20importantly%20mandate%20their%20enforcement%20by%20a%20judiciary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20Constitution%20is%20a%20binding%20legal%20document%20not%20a%20statement%20of%20political%20intent%20to%20be%20enforced%20at%20the%20discretion%20of%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oyez.org%2Fcases%2F1789-1850%2F5us137%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EMarbury%20versus%20Madison%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20decided%20in%201803%20in%20the%20US%2C%20established%20judicial%20review%2C%20which%20laid%20the%20foundation%20for%20modern-day%20constitutional%20and%20administrative%20law.%20The%20judgment%20came%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20the%20US%20was%20being%20attacked%20by%20Thomas%20Jefferson%20and%20his%20followers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judgment%20of%20Justice%20Marshall%20established%20for%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20the%20United%20States%20the%20apex%20position%20of%20final%20interpreter%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20There%20is%20little%20disagreement%20among%20scholars%20around%20the%20world%20on%20the%20principle%20that%C2%A0%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Ea%20law%20repugnant%20to%20the%20Constitution%20is%20void%2C%20and%20that%20courts%2C%20as%20well%20as%20other%20departments%2C%20are%20bound%20by%20that%20instrument%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20what%20constitutionalism%20is%20about.%20That%20was%20the%20end%20of%20the%20doctrine%20of%20supremacy%20of%20the%20Parliament%20or%20the%20Congress%2C%20by%20giving%20the%20court%20a%20final%20voice%20on%20the%20legal%20and%20constitutional%20propriety%20of%20acts%20of%20any%20member%20of%20the%20Executive%20or%20an%20Act%20of%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOurs%20is%20a%20Constitution%20that%20explicitly%20states%2C%20in%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-13-laws-inconsistent-with-or-in-derogation-of-the-fundamental-rights%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DArticle%252013%252C%2520Constitution%2520of%2520India%25201950%26amp%3Btext%3Dinconsistency%252C%2520be%2520void.-%2C(2)%2520The%2520State%2520shall%2520not%2520make%2520any%2520law%2520which%2520takes%2Cof%2520the%2520contravention%252C%2520be%2520void.%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Article%2013%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20all%20laws%2C%20customs%2C%20and%20usages%20inconsistent%20with%20or%20repugnant%20to%20our%20fundamental%20rights%20shall%20to%20the%20extent%20of%20the%20repugnancy%20be%20void.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20very%20existence%20of%20Articles%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-32-remedies-for-enforcement-of-rights-conferred-by-this-part%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DArticle%252032%252C%2520Constitution%2520of%2520India%2Cby%2520this%2520Part%2520is%2520guaranteed.%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A032%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-226-power-of-high-courts-to-issue-certain-writs%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0226%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20allow%20direct%20access%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20the%20High%20Courts%20respectively%2C%20establishes%20the%20enforceability%20of%20our%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20hierarchy%20of%20norms%20for%20the%20governance%20of%20our%20society%20and%20the%20Constitution%20is%20at%20the%20top%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20our%20Constitutional%20rights%20as%20citizens%20now%20appear%20to%20be%20unenforceable.%20Our%20elected%20representatives%20now%20treat%20the%20Constitution%20not%20as%20a%20normative%20and%20enforceable%20document%20but%20as%20a%20political%20document%20alone%2C%20a%20statement%20of%20intent%20to%20be%20enforced%20selectively%20at%20its%20discretion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20this%20approach%20to%20the%20Constitution%20that%20the%20court%20has%20been%20unable%20to%20correct%20and%20on%20which%20it%20has%20failed%20to%20demand%20accountability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20failed%20to%20protect%20electoral%20democracy%2C%20the%20health%20of%20our%20economy%2C%20our%20own%20health%2C%20federalism%2C%20and%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhether%20it%20was%20demonetisation%20and%20its%20impact%20on%20the%20country%2C%20the%20right%20of%20our%20elected%20representatives%20to%20remain%20in%20office%20without%20being%20subjected%20to%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fbangalore%2Fbig-conspiracy-operation-lotus-karnataka-siddaramaiah-shivakumar-9004089%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Operation%20Lotus%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20the%20disappearance%20of%20a%20state%20and%20its%20conversion%20to%20a%20Union%20territory%2C%20the%20court%20deferred%20to%20the%20wisdom%20of%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day%2C%20sometimes%20explicitly%20stating%20that%20it%20was%20not%20the%20function%20of%20the%20court%20to%20interfere%20with%20government%20policy%20or%20under%20the%20doctrine%20of%20not%20wanting%20to%20enter%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Epolitical%20thicket%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D%20laying%20claim%20to%20work%20on%20the%20theory%20of%20separation%20of%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cb%3EGradual%20repudiation%20by%20the%20court%20of%20its%20core%20function%20of%20judicial%20review%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20appears%20almost%20as%20if%20our%20rights%20are%20not%20enforceable%20anymore%20and%20there%20is%20an%20attempt%20to%20return%20to%20the%20idea%20that%20governments%20are%20benevolent%20decision-makers%20and%20know%20best%20what%20to%20do.%20The%20Constitution%20has%20been%20robbed%20not%20only%20of%20its%20spirit%20but%20also%20of%20its%20binding%20normative%20nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20government%20of%20India%20has%20not%20lost%20a%20single%20judgment%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202023%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20four%20most%20significant%20challenges%20to%20major%20decisions%20of%20the%20government%2C%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fdissecting-the-majority-and-minority-opinions-in-the-demonetisation-judgment%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0demonetisation%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(save%20for%20one%20dissent)%2C%20the%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fmaharashtra-political-crisis-judgment-a-detailed-analysis%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0swearing%20in%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20a%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)-led%20government%20in%20Maharashtra%20by%20the%20governor%2C%20the%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fin-re-article-370-judgment-supreme-court-ratifies-one-vidhan-pradhan-and-nishan%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0abolition%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-370-temporary-provisions-with-respect-to-the-state-of-jammu-and-kashmir%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Article%20370%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fmarriage-equality-judgment-an-explainer%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0challenge%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F15480%2F1%2Fspecial_marriage_act.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Special%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201954%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0which%20excludes%20queer%20marriage%2C%20all%20were%20decided%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20prominent%20feature%20of%20judgments%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202023%20has%20been%20that%20even%20when%20the%20declaration%20of%20law%20was%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20petitioner%2C%20the%20operative%20Order%20was%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20in%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fcategory%2Fmaharashtra-political-crisis%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3Ci%3ESubhash%20Desai%20versus%20Principal%20Secretary%2C%20Governor%20of%20Maharashtra%20and%20Ors%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0held%20that%20the%20action%20of%20the%20governor%20in%20swearing%20in%20a%20new%20government%20was%20bad%20in%20law%20and%20yet%20the%20government%20was%20allowed%20to%20remain%20in%20place%2C%20and%20it%20was%20left%20to%20the%20speaker%20to%20decide%20on%20the%20applications%20for%20disqualification%20of%20members%20of%20legislative%20assembly%20(MLAs).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20of%20writing%2C%20more%20than%20one%20year%20after%20the%20chief%20minister%20was%20unlawfully%20sworn%20in%2C%20the%20BJP%20remains%20the%20ruling%20party%20and%20the%20speaker%20has%20taken%20no%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20came%20to%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fpdf%2FLU%2Farticle_370.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3Ci%3EIn%20Re%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0%3Ci%3EArticle%20370%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%20even%20though%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20that%20the%20amendment%20to%20Article%20370%C2%A0%3Ci%3Eproviso%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Evia%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-367-interpretation%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Article%20367%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0rout%20was%C2%A0%3Ci%3Eultra%20vires%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20it%20ruled%20that%20the%20abolition%20of%20Article%20370%20by%20the%20Presidential%20Order%20was%20valid%20since%20the%20President%20could%2C%20in%20any%20event%2C%20abolish%20Article%20370%20by%20resorting%20to%20Article%20307(3)%20independent%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ci%3Eproviso%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Eunilaterally%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20discussion%20of%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20President%20during%20an%20Emergency%20was%20unnecessary%2C%20the%20abolition%20could%20occur%20with%20or%20without%20an%20Emergency.%20On%20the%20question%20of%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20reorganisation%20of%20the%20state%20into%20a%20Union%20territory%2C%20the%20court%20accepted%20the%20statement%20of%20the%20Solicitor%20General%20of%20India%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20not%20binding%20on%20the%20Parliament%20%E2%80%93%20that%20elections%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20will%20be%20called%20before%20September%202024%2C%20rather%20than%20giving%20a%20%3Ci%3Emandamus%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Eto%20conduct%20the%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20came%20to%20same-sex%20marriage%2C%20the%20court%20sent%20the%20petitioners%20back%20to%20the%20government%20to%20work%20out%20a%20new%20law%20laying%20down%20guidelines%20for%20a%20violence-free%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20party%20believes%20that%20our%20jurisprudence%20can%20be%20written%20and%20rewritten%2C%20and%20that%20it%20is%20time%20to%20return%20to%20our%20culture%20which%20goes%20back%20to%20Vedic%20times%20%E2%80%93%20to%20a%20time%20before%20repeated%20invasions%20by%20%E2%80%98foreigners%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20believe%20that%20our%20laws%20are%20to%20be%20found%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Ci%3EManusmriti%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0and%20the%C2%A0%3Ci%3EArthashastra%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0and%20we%20must%20return%20to%20our%20roots.%20Could%20these%20ideas%20perhaps%20be%20permeating%20into%20the%20judiciary%20through%20a%20process%20of%20osmosis%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20has%20any%20value%2C%20it%20is%20that%20it%20contains%20Article%20226%20and%20Article%2032%20which%20enable%20the%20courts%20to%20give%20binding%20directions%20to%20the%20government%2C%20which%20are%20the%20heart%20and%20soul%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20It%20is%20these%20Articles%20that%20are%20endangered%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20body%20of%20the%20judiciary%20has%20self-inflicted%20wounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20question%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20has%20all%20this%20been%20achieved%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20authors%20such%20as%20Tarunabh%20Khaitan%20have%20expressed%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D3367266%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0view%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20this%20has%20been%20achieved%20by%20killing%20the%20Constitution%20with%20a%20thousand%20cuts.%20True%20that%20is%20for%20the%20legislature.%20But%20what%20about%20the%20judiciary%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOthers%20have%20said%20that%20when%20governments%20are%20authoritarian%20and%20majoritarian%2C%20the%20courts%20are%20weak.%20But%20then%20why%20have%20an%20independent%20judiciary%20at%20all%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Flead%2Fthe-fear-of-executive-courts%2Farticle25735185.ece%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0others%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0call%20it%20an%20%E2%80%98Executive%20court%E2%80%99%2C%20an%20inaccurate%20description%20since%20Executive%20courts%20do%20not%20normally%20have%20the%20power%20of%20judicial%20review%20at%20all%2C%20as%20in%20the%20former%20USSR.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20have%20even%20suggested%20that%20the%20courts%20are%20being%20blackmailed.%20For%20this%2C%20there%20can%20be%20no%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20can%20be%20a%20combination%20of%20these%20factors%20but%20there%20is%20something%20deeper%20than%20these%20factors%20to%20be%20investigated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20this%2C%20let%20us%20look%20at%20our%20not-too-distant%20constitutional%20past%2C%20the%20declaration%20of%20the%20Emergency%20and%20the%20resistance%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20struggle%20against%20the%20Emergency%20demonstrated%20both%20the%20strength%20and%20the%20malleability%20of%20constitutionalism.%20It%20demonstrated%20how%20the%20political%20process%2C%20parties%20and%20individuals%20approach%20a%20written%20document%2C%20namely%20the%20Constitution%2C%20to%20shape%20their%20approach%20and%20attitude%20to%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20struggle%20against%20the%20Emergency%20was%20to%20restore%20the%C2%A0%3Ci%3Estatus%20quo%20ante%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0politically%20and%20later%20to%20amend%20the%20Constitution%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20right%20to%20life%20is%20guaranteed%20and%20can%20never%20be%20suspended.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%2C%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20who%20was%20instrumental%20in%20imposing%20the%20Emergency%2C%20and%20Jayprakash%20Narayan%2C%20who%20led%20the%20struggle%20to%20revoke%20the%20Emergency%2C%20accused%20each%20other%20of%20being%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Edictators%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Efascists%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D%E2%80%94%20meaning%20thereby%20they%20saw%20the%20other%20deviating%20from%20the%20path%20of%20liberal%20democratic%20principles%20on%20which%20the%20Constitution%20and%20Indian%20polity%20was%20envisioned%20to%20be%20founded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20of%20them%20claimed%20allegiance%20to%20the%20Constitution.%20Speaking%20of%20the%20events%20which%20led%20to%20the%20imposition%20of%20the%20Emergency%2C%20namely%20the%20protests%20led%20by%20Jayprakash%20Narayan%20and%20the%20students%E2%80%99%20movements%2C%20Bipan%20Chandra%20points%20out%20in%20his%20book%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpenguin.co.in%2Fbook%2Fin-the-name-of-democracy%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3Ci%3EIn%20the%20Name%20of%20Democracy%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EThe%20defence%20of%20Indian%20democracy%20seems%20to%20have%20been%20the%20main%20justification%20for%20both%20the%20J.P.%20movement%20and%20the%20Emergency%20regime%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20hierarchy%20of%20norms%20for%20the%20governance%20of%20our%20society%2C%20both%20accepted%20that%20the%20Constitution%20is%20at%20the%20top.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20today%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20party%20looks%20at%20liberalism%20as%20an%20import%2C%20they%20yearn%20for%20a%20return%20to%20Ram%20Rajya%2C%20the%20codes%20of%C2%A0%3Ci%3EManusmriti%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Eand%20the%20governance%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ci%3EArthashastra%3C%2Fi%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESitting%20judges%20now%20refer%20to%20these%20texts%20to%20justify%20their%20decisions%20at%20a%20rate%20that%20can%20only%20be%20described%20as%20alarming.%20Theology%2C%20whatever%20name%20is%20used%20to%20refer%20to%20it%E2%80%94%20custom%2C%20culture%20or%20religion%E2%80%94%20has%20for%20many%20become%20the%20source%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20change%20is%20symbolised%20in%20our%20public%20life%20by%20the%20installation%20of%20the%20Sengol%20in%20the%20new%20Parliament%20building%2C%20a%20symbol%20of%20kingship%20rather%20than%20of%20Republicanism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20upcoming%20consecration%20of%20the%20Ram%20Temple%E2%80%94%20built%20by%20a%20trust%20set%20up%20by%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%E2%80%94%20by%20constitutional%20functionaries%20in%20the%20name%20of%20exercising%20the%20right%20to%20religion%2C%20the%20separation%20between%20religion%20and%20the%20State%20is%20imploding.%20What%20tsunamis%20this%20admixture%20will%20produce%20only%20time%20will%20tell.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20also%20is%20how%20this%20appeal%20to%20customs%20and%20culture%20impacted%20the%20judiciary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20appears%20to%20have%20had%20a%20direct%20impact%20on%20the%20judiciary%20as%20they%20too%20have%20started%20appealing%20to%20culture%20and%20customs%20to%20justify%20imposing%20restrictions%20on%20fundamental%20rights%20or%20writing%20them%20out%20of%20existence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENothing%20illustrates%20this%20better%20than%20the%20judgment%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmarriage-equality-supreme-court-decision%5C%22%3EJustice%20Narasimha%20in%20the%20marriage%20equality%20case%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judgment%20shows%20that%2C%20mirroring%20the%20Executive%2C%20our%20courts%20have%20set%20up%20a%20norm%20above%20the%20norm%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20i.e.%2C%20culture%2C%20and%20will%20not%20enforce%20the%20text%20of%20the%20Constitution%20when%20it%20conflicts%20with%20the%20culture%2C%20howsoever%20defined.%20It%20is%20indeed%20the%20repudiation%20of%20the%20judicial%20function.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20legal%20community%20needs%20to%20be%20vigilant%20to%20prevent%20this%20failing%20court%20since%20the%20future%20of%20the%20rights%20of%20citizens%20seems%20to%20be%20in%20jeopardy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20year%202023%20has%20been%20the%20year%20of%20the%20%3Ci%3Esurajmukhi%3C%2Fi%3E%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F925631%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20court%20which%20held%20that%20Hinduism%20is%20a%20way%20of%20life%20and%20not%20religion%20alone%2C%20the%20marriage%20equality%20judgment%20is%20the%20only%20judgment%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20legitimising%20culture%20as%20the%20measure%20of%20whether%20a%20restriction%20on%20a%20right%20was%20reasonable%20or%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20note%20that%20Article%2013%2C%20which%20declares%20all%20laws%20that%20violate%20fundamental%20rights%20void%2C%20defines%20law%20to%20include%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Ecustom%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D%20but%20it%20does%20not%20include%20%E2%80%98culture%E2%80%99%20as%20law.%20Yet%20today%20we%20have%20a%20judgment%20that%20clearly%20permits%20culture%20to%20trump%20fundamental%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20cultural%20test%20of%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Ereasonableness%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D%20can%20be%20used%20to%20uphold%20governmental%20action%2C%20why%20can%20it%20not%20be%20used%20to%20interpret%20the%20Constitution%20itself%20or%20the%20validity%20of%20a%20constitutional%20amendment%20for%20that%20matter%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F257876%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EKeshavananda%20Bharati%20versus%20State%20of%20Kerala%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20decided%20in%201973%2C%20held%20that%20the%20basic%20features%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20such%20as%20fundamental%20rights%2C%20secularism%2C%20democracy%20and%20federalism%2C%20could%20not%20be%20amended%20even%20by%20a%20Constitutional%20amendment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20today%20we%20see%20the%20same%20result%20as%20we%20would%20by%20an%20amendment%20by%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20norm%20higher%20than%20and%20inconsistent%20with%20the%20values%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20new%20set%20of%20practices%20has%20replaced%20constitutionalism%20and%20legality%20and%20has%20been%20elevated%20to%20the%20level%20above%20the%20Constitution%20with%20reference%20to%20which%20the%20Constitution%20and%20its%20basic%20features%20are%20to%20be%20interpreted.%20Rights%2C%20as%20we%20know%20them%2C%20are%20replaced%20by%20duties%2C%20negating%20the%20entire%20chapter%20on%20fundamental%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20fundamental%20duties%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fconstitution-day-fundamental-duties-should-be-the-first-priority-of-citizens-says-pm-modi%2Farticleshow%2F95782187.cms%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0now%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0take%20precedence%20over%20our%20fundamental%20rights.%20We%20must%20all%20do%20our%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fgovernor-tathagata-roy-most-controversial-statements-5594182%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3Ekartavya%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20without%20any%20expectation%20of%20freedom.%20A%20new%20language%20of%20politics%20and%20consequentially%20law%20has%20been%20invented%20in%20place%20of%20constitutionalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20told%20that%20there%20is%20an%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fhindu-dharma-has-taken-over-constitutional-values-says-indira-jaising-at-the-sixth-neelabh-mishra-lecture%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3Eintrinsic%20dharma%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20people%20of%20India%20which%20is%20ancient%20and%20predates%20the%20Constitution.%20Once%20a%20norm%20above%20the%20Constitution%20is%20created%2C%20it%20is%20easy%20to%20see%20why%20there%20is%20no%20need%20to%20amend%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20a%20transformation%20of%20an%20unparalleled%20kind%20in%20the%20last%2010%20years.%20It%20is%20not%20just%20a%20thousand%20cuts%20or%20an%20undeclared%20Emergency%2C%20the%20very%20norms%20by%20which%20we%20govern%20ourselves%20have%20been%20changed.%20The%20tragic%20part%20is%20that%20all%20this%20has%20been%20achieved%20through%20the%20judiciary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20needs%20the%20judiciary%20to%20legitimise%20its%20political%20agenda%20and%20achieve%20the%20transformation%20of%20the%20State%20from%20a%20secular%20to%20a%20theocratic%20one.%20What%20we%20are%20seeing%20is%20that%20the%20text%20of%20the%20Constitution%20remains%20in%20place%20while%20its%20core%20values%20of%20justice%2C%20liberty%2C%20equality%2C%20fraternity%20and%20dignity%20have%20been%20repudiated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20those%20who%20say%20we%20are%20decolonising%20our%20law%2C%20it%20must%20be%20said%20that%20the%20Constitution%20including%20its%20preamble%20is%C2%A0%3Ci%3Esui%20generis.%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0The%20Constitution%20of%20India%20represents%20a%20revolutionary%20break%20from%20everything%20that%20went%20before%20it%20and%20hence%20the%20ideology%20of%20the%20past%E2%80%94%20political%20or%20religious%20cannot%20be%20used%20to%20interpret%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20criminal%20laws%20did%20not%20need%20a%20repeal%2C%20if%20reform%20was%20needed%2C%20they%20could%20have%20been%20amended.%20It%20is%20false%20to%20suggest%20that%20they%20are%20part%20of%20an%20effort%20of%20decolonisation%20to%20achieve%20citizen-centric%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChanging%20names%20does%20not%20make%20laws%20anti-colonial%20just%20like%20changing%20names%20of%20cities%20does%20not%20transform%20them%20into%20clean%2C%20green%20and%20liveable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cb%3EDeceitful%20devices%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20setting%20up%20cultural%20norms%20to%20govern%20the%20country%2C%20many%20deceitful%20devices%20have%20been%20used%2C%20leaving%20it%20to%20the%20judiciary%20to%20sort%20out%20the%20mess.%20Money%20Bills%20have%20been%20used%20to%20create%20crimes%2C%20to%20circumvent%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotifications%20have%20been%20issued%20where%20legislation%20was%20required%2C%20as%20in%20the%20case%20of%20demonetisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20left%20to%20the%20dissenting%20judge%20to%20point%20out%20that%20the%20law%20had%20been%20circumvented.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cb%3EHow%20are%20judges%3C%2Fb%3E%C2%A0%3Cb%3Eappointed%3A%20Who%20%E2%80%98mans%E2%80%99%20our%20courts%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20courts%20are%20literally%20maned.%20During%20the%20tenure%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20Dr%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud-led%20collegium%2C%20which%20has%20been%20relatively%20long%2C%2014%20judges%20have%20been%20appointed%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Not%20one%20among%20them%20is%20a%20woman%20or%20from%20the%20Scheduled%20Tribe%20or%20Scheduled%20Caste%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20an%20impressive%20statue%20of%20Dr%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20in%20band%20and%20gown%20was%20installed%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20the%20CJI.%20We%20seem%20to%20honour%20Dr%20Ambedkar%20more%20in%20brick%20and%20stone%20than%20in%20having%20regard%20to%20Articles%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-15-prohibition-of-discrimination-on-grounds-of-religion-race-caste-sex-or-place-of-birth%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A015%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.constitutionofindia.net%2Farticles%2Farticle-17-abolition-of-untouchability%2F%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A017%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cb%3EAnd%20what%20are%20the%20politics%20of%20the%20judges%20appointed%3C%2Fb%3E%3F%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20that%20our%20high%20courts%20and%20Supreme%20Court%20judges%20are%20self-appointed%20by%20the%20collegium%2C%20it%20is%20the%20judiciary%20alone%20that%20bears%20the%20burden%20of%20making%20appointees%20of%20fair-minded%20and%20independent%20judges%20of%20their%20choice%2C%20and%20of%20ensuring%20caste%2C%20religious%2C%20and%20gender%20diversity%20in%20our%20courts.%20In%20this%2C%20it%20has%20failed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20us%20look%20at%20a%20highly%20controversial%20appointment%20to%20the%20High%20Court%20of%20Madras%2C%20that%20of%20Lakshmana%20Chandra%20Victoria%20Gowri.%20She%20was%20part%20of%20a%20women%E2%80%99s%20organisation%20of%20the%20BJP.%20Her%20speeches%20in%20that%20regard%20are%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20and%20they%20can%20rightly%20be%20characterised%20as%20being%20%E2%80%98hate%20speech%E2%80%99%2C%20proscribed%20by%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20she%20likened%20Islam%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Egreen%20terror%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%9D%20and%20Christianity%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3Ewhite%20terro%3C%2Fi%3Er%E2%80%9D.%20Yet%20she%20came%20to%20be%20appointed%20as%20a%20judge%20of%20a%20high%20court.%20When%20the%20news%20broke%2C%20the%20lawyers%20in%20Chennai%20were%20so%20outraged%20that%20they%20filed%20a%20petition%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20challenging%20her%20appointment%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20she%20was%20not%20eligible%20to%20be%20a%20judge%2C%20in%20that%20her%20public%20utterances%20were%20against%20constitutional%20morality%20and%20showed%20bias%20towards%20minorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20confusion%20relating%20to%20whether%20or%20not%20the%20collegium%20was%20aware%20of%20her%20utterance%2C%20the%20matter%20was%20listed%20before%20a%20Bench%20comprising%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20and%20B.R.%20Gavai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20was%20hastily%20dismissed%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20once%20appointed%2C%20no%20challenge%20to%20the%20appointment%20could%20be%20made%20as%20the%20ground%20of%20challenge%20is%20limited%20to%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20or%20not%20the%20person%20was%20qualified%20as%20required%20by%20the%20Constitution%2C%20namely%20the%20person%20concerned%20should%20have%20been%20a%20practising%20advocate%20for%20at%20least%2010%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20begging%20the%20question%20raised%2C%20namely%2C%20whether%20a%20person%20who%20had%20exhibited%20her%20hatred%20of%20religious%20minorities%20was%20eligible%20to%20be%20a%20judge%20of%20a%20Constitutional%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20appointment%20was%20made%20with%20the%20full%20consciousness%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20she%20had%20made%20those%20speeches.%20She%20was%20administered%20the%20oath%20of%20appointment%20while%20her%20appointment%20was%20still%20under%20challenge.%20Welcome%20to%20the%20ideological%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMagical%20transformations%20do%20not%20occur%20when%20judges%20sit%20on%20Benches.%20The%20real%20name%20of%20the%20game%20is%C2%A0%3Ci%3EKoun%20Banega%20CJI%3C%2Fi%3E%3F%20Seniority%2C%20which%20was%20the%20primary%20criterion%20for%20the%20appointment%20of%20judges%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20from%20high%20courts%2C%20was%20given%20a%20go%20by%20picking%20up%20judges%20from%20high%20courts%20who%20could%20go%20on%20to%20become%20the%20CJI%2C%20given%20the%20young%20age%20at%20which%20they%20are%20picked%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppointments%20and%20transfers%20suggested%20are%20not%20made.%20The%20Constitution%20has%20offered%20no%20method%20by%20which%20the%20recommendations%20of%20judges%20can%20be%20implemented%20by%20issuing%20a%C2%A0%3Ci%3Emandamus%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Eto%20the%20President%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudges%20who%20have%20been%20recommended%20for%20transfer%20to%20other%20courts%2C%20more%20particularly%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Funion-government-notifies-transfer-of-five-judges%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0four%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0judges%20from%20Gujarat%2C%20have%20remained%20in%20the%20comfortable%20climate%20of%20the%20state%20despite%20the%20recommendation%20having%20come%20months%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20of%20writing%2C%3Ca%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22internal%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Ftwo-days-after-justice-kauls-retirement-cji-convened-collegium-meet-recommends-new-chief-justices-of-five-high-courts%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0news%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0has%20come%20in%20that%20two%20days%20after%20one%20of%20the%20collegium%20judges%20retired%2C%20chief%20justices%20have%20been%20appointed%20to%20five%20high%20courts%2C%20giving%20the%20clear%20impression%20that%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20retiring%20judge%20was%20avoided.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20we%20are%20looking%20at%20is%20a%20collapse%20of%20the%20judiciary%20from%20within.%20We%20must%20take%20it%20that%20every%20judge%20who%20is%20appointed%20has%20been%20appointed%20with%20the%20concurrence%20of%20the%20collegium.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20two%20avatars%20of%20a%20judge%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20seen%20judges%20before%20and%20after%20they%20become%20chief%20justices%20of%20the%20court.%20Something%20definitely%20changes%20when%20they%20become%20chief%20justices%2C%20maybe%20it%20is%20the%20power%20that%20comes%20with%20being%20the%20%E2%80%98first%20among%20equals%E2%80%99%20but%20their%20sense%20of%20power%20certainly%20increases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20source%20of%20power%20is%20that%20of%20the%20Master%20of%20the%20Roster.%20The%20assignment%20of%20cases%20to%20particular%20judges%20is%20the%20function%20of%20the%20master.%20The%20practice%20and%20procedure%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20been%20that%20a%20case%20will%20be%20heard%20by%20a%20Bench%20that%20issued%20notice%20on%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20case%20one%20of%20the%20judges%20is%20not%20available%20or%20is%20on%20a%20different%20Bench%2C%20the%20case%20is%20assigned%20to%20the%20senior%20of%20the%20two%20judges%20and%20if%20the%20senior%20for%20some%20reason%20is%20not%20available%20then%20to%20the%20junior%20of%20the%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESee%2C%20for%20example%2C%20Paragraph%206%20of%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fpdf%2FLU%2Fppop2017.pdf%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%3Ci%3EHandbook%20of%20Practice%20and%20Procedure%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Para%206%20specifically%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3Ci%3EIf%20the%20first%20coram%20is%20not%20available%20on%20a%20particular%20day%20on%20account%20of%20retirement%2C%20the%20case%20shall%20be%20listed%20before%20the%20judge%20constituting%20the%20second%20coram.%20If%20the%20second%20coram%20is%20also%20not%20available%2C%20the%20case%20shall%20not%20be%20listed%20on%20that%20day%3C%2Fi%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20practice%20was%20wantonly%20abandoned%2C%20making%20it%20possible%20to%20assign%20any%20case%20to%20any%20Bench.%20We%20have%20a%20herd%20of%20lawyers%20Bench-hunting%2C%20now%20are%20we%20witnessing%20the%20registry%20Bench-hunting%3F%20Efforts%20by%20senior%20lawyers%20to%20meet%20the%20Master%20of%20the%20Roster%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20have%20failed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20visible%20of%20our%20judges%20in%20the%20public%20domain%2C%20the%20CJI%2C%20is%20the%20most%20inaccessible%20to%20the%20Bar%2C%20which%20is%20meant%20to%20be%20an%20equal%20partner%20in%20the%20protection%20of%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20judiciary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOccasional%20visits%20to%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FTheLeaflet_in%2Fstatus%2F1722856493635207648%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0canteen%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0or%20the%20singing%20of%20children%E2%80%99s%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D5RZWwHlLBfs%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0jingles%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20Christmas%20is%20no%20substitutive%20for%20interaction%20between%20the%20Bench%20and%20Bar%20on%20matters%20of%20judicial%20administration.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22external%20noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fsenior-advocate-dushyant-dave-writes-open-letter-to-cji-on-shifting-of-cases-from-one-bench-to-another-in-disregard-of-sc-rules%2Farticle67610056.ece%5C%22%20data-wpel-link%3D%5C%22external%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Open%20letters%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0never%20to%20be%20replied%20to%20are%20all%20we%20are%20left%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20time%20for%20judges%20to%20wake%20up%20and%20understand%20that%20it%20is%20lawyers%20alone%20who%20stand%20as%20a%20barrier%20between%20the%20Bench%20and%20the%20Executive.%20It%20is%20no%20doubt%20a%20tragedy%20that%20the%20Bar%20today%20is%20as%20polarised%20as%20civil%20society%2C%20and%20the%20Bar%20has%20failed%20in%20its%20duty%20of%20fiercely%20defending%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20judiciary%20from%20the%20Executive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20we%20not%20only%20have%20a%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Bar%20Council%20of%20India%20but%20also%20a%20President%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Bar%20Association%20who%20credits%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20in%20their%20public%20statements%20for%20all%20that%20goes%20in%20the%20name%20of%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cb%3EUnfinished%20agenda%3C%2Fb%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20achieved%20its%20agenda%20of%20building%20a%20Ram%20Mandir%20and%20the%20abolition%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20what%20is%20the%20unfinished%20agenda%20of%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%3F%20Is%20it%20that%20of%20the%20Uniform%20Ci